snippet.textDisplay: The main problem lies with the speed & arrangement. The song was made for a courtesan in the movie - therefore you can find a lazy, flirty and sensual vibe throughout in Ashaji's version - . It was never about the gamakams. Here Karsh Kale increased the tala (Speed) hence the singer has no room for relaxed singing, which was essential for the lyrics. Monali is a great singer, but she struggles to keep up with the pace - when u remix u've to ensure u don't lose the soul of the composition!
